mperature and\nthe electronic properties are also dominated by chalcogen p-orbitals. Our study\ndemonstrates that the intercalation of palladium leads to the suppression of\nthe CDW order and the emergence of the superconductivity. Our finding could\nprovide an ideal model system for comprehensive studies of the interplay\nbetween CDW and superconductivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2013 16:17:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-01-15"}
